    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="778"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2938: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 27, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. Little change during the week in the political situation. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Diario de la Marina</hi> permitted to resume publication 25th. Government
                    announces discovery of abortive attempt at uprising Christmas eve. Colonel
                    Hevia, prominent leader of Unión Nacionalista, and several other alleged
                    conspirators arrested yesterday and confined in military prison pending trial by
                    court martial.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
